B.PQ=new A.f1("Users were spending too long on review","Hotjar recordings showed users spending 5 to 8 minutes on the Review Details stage, repeatedly scanning the page and revisiting content before deciding whether to continue.")
B.Q_=new A.f1("Users were leaving the flow to find reassurance","Some users left the quote journey and visited the main website to better understand what was included in their policy, indicating that the review experience itself was not providing enough clarity.")
B.PT=new A.f1("Behaviour suggested friction and overload","Session recordings showed long pauses, repeated scrolling, and rage clicks on non-interactive elements, all of which suggested confusion rather than confident progression.")
B.PU=new A.f1("Competitors handled trust more effectively","Competitor and aggregator-linked journeys used stronger brand alignment, more visible trust signals, and clearer summaries of policy information at comparable decision points.")
B.PR=new A.f1("The interface lacked consistency","Buttons, pop-ups, close states, and text formatting varied across the flow, which weakened the sense of polish and overall reliability.")
