B.Qi=new A.d_("Objective","Improve clarity, trust, and completion")
B.Qa=new A.d_("Users","Pet owners reviewing quotes online")
B.Qg=new A.d_("Constraints","FCA compliance, legacy continuity, MudBlazor")
B.Qc=new A.d_("Success measure","Completion rate and user confidence")
B.JC=s([B.Qi,B.Qa,B.Qg,B.Qc],t.GN)
B.QB=new A.zt("Perfect Pet Insurance\u2019s quote journey allows users to select cover, review the details of their policy, and then continue towards purchase. The Review Details stage sits at the point where a user stops to assess what they are actually buying: what level of cover they have chosen, what is included, and whether the overall price and proposition feel right for them. It is a critical point in the journey because it is where uncertainty tends to surface most clearly.","The existing experience made that assessment harder than it needed to be. The page relied heavily on dense text blocks, offered limited visual hierarchy, and lacked the reassurance cues needed to support confident decision-making. For users arriving from aggregator journeys, this was especially problematic. Many were encountering the brand mid-funnel, with limited context, and needed a quick, clear understanding of what they were reviewing. The redesign therefore needed to make the journey easier to understand without reducing essential policy detail or compromising compliance.",B.JC,null)
B.QI=new A.ft("Reviewed behavioural evidence","I began by reviewing session recordings, internal feedback, and the existing journey to ensure the redesign was grounded in user behaviour rather than visual preference alone.")
B.QG=new A.ft("Benchmarked the category","I reviewed other pet insurance and aggregator-linked experiences to understand how comparable journeys used structure, reassurance, and branding to support decision-making.")
B.QF=new A.ft("Conducted a heuristic audit","Using Nielsen Norman heuristics, I evaluated the existing flow against established usability principles such as clarity, consistency, and visibility of system status.")
B.QC=new A.ft("Explored solutions within constraints","Working with the BA and front-end developer, I developed layout directions that improved legibility and trust while remaining realistic within MudBlazor and compliant with required policy language.")
B.QD=new A.ft("Validated the redesign internally","Once the revised Review Details stage had been finalised, it went through internal usability testing to assess comprehension, confidence, and task completion before live experimentation.")
B.Hq=s([B.QI,B.QG,B.QF,B.QC,B.QD],t.DD)
B.QL=new A.zu("Approach",B.Hq,null)
B.QO=new A.zv("The issue was not a lack of demand. It was the amount of effort users had to expend to understand the product and feel confident proceeding.","Summary of the core finding across research and internal feedback",null)
